Brayden Travis, from St Charles County, Missouri, has battled drug addiction since he was 15 and overdosed on heroin in early March . 
 The 18-year-old was left without medical attention for seven hours and suffered a stroke and severe brain damage . 
 Doctors told his parents he might be left in a vegetative state but he is now conscious and has made small improvements . 
 His mother shared a photo of him in hospital in a bid to deter others from taking drugs; the post has been shared more than 337,000 times . 
 